Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.83,0:00:03.60,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}A racing second hand, a shooting comet!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.60,0:00:07.63,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Conan's logic works fast\Non hearts tired by modern society!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.63,0:00:11.20,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Today's case is an impossible crime!\NMoney comes and goes!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.20,0:00:12.84,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.84,0:00:14.71,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.71,0:00:16.85,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.06,0:01:44.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Mahjong"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.59,0:01:47.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,({\i1}ryan-pin{\i0} = two)
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.59,0:01:47.72,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Should I lose the ryan-pin?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.72,0:01:50.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,({\i1}sha-bo{\i0} = double-pair)
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.72,0:01:50.73,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}A sha-bo would make the wait pointless...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.73,0:01:54.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wha...?! Are you messing\Nwith my pieces {\i1}again{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.50,0:02:00.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, come on. You're doing well tonight.\NConsider it a handicap!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.44,0:02:01.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,(winning move)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.44,0:02:01.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Ron{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.94,0:02:06.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Menchin{\i0}, {\i1}ipeiko{\i0}, {\i1}dora{\i0}, {\i1}dora{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.38,0:02:09.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,({\i1}baiman{\i0} = double)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.38,0:02:09.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-That's a {\i1}baiman{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.61,0:02:11.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I lose!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.11,0:02:13.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're leaving, Okano?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.52,0:02:17.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I have no luck tonight.\NI'll be off now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.42,0:02:20.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now we need another player...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.45,0:02:21.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's ask Hida{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.96,0:02:23.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hida{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.29,0:02:29.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He runs that finance company.\NHe loves Mahjong.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.64,0:02:31.60,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"President's Office"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.57,0:02:38.32,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Mitsuhiro Hida (53)\NPresident of Hida Financial
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.97,0:02:38.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,10 million. I'm all smiles tonight!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.38,0:02:43.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, this is Hida Financial.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.58,0:02:47.04,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Ah, Hida{\rHonorifics - Radio\be10}-san{\r\be10}! You're still there!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.04,0:02:48.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's you, Hasegawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.52,0:02:50.45,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Do you hear this?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.45,0:02:55.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We need another player,\Nso I thought I'd ask...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.92,0:03:00.50,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I'll be right there once\NI'm done counting this money!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.50,0:03:02.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.20,0:03:06.22,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I'll be there in half an hour!\NPlay without me until then!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.27,0:03:10.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Says it'll be 30 minutes\Nand to keep playing until then.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.94,0:03:13.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Great, then I'll play until then!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.64,0:03:15.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.52,0:03:17.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no, you won't!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.41,0:03:20.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!\NI was wondering where you were!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.95,0:03:23.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You brought him here,\Ndidn't you, Dad?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.95,0:03:25.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.42,0:03:26.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.62,0:03:30.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, would you wanna\Nplay for half an hour or so?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.59,0:03:34.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I {\i1}hate{\i0} that stupid,\Ngloomy grownup game!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.27,0:03:38.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Ron{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.17,0:03:41.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A {\i1}dai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}-gen{\i0}, {\i1}su-an-ko{\i0},\Nand {\i1}tsui-i-so{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.50,0:03:45.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A triple {\i1}yakuman{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.01,0:03:46.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I won again!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.52,0:03:47.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.78,0:03:50.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is Hida{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.35,0:03:51.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give him a call.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.89,0:04:00.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Weird, he's not answering.\NBut his lights are still on.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.26,0:04:01.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe something happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.76,0:04:05.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, yeah, he was strangely\Nflustered when I called him earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.69,0:04:07.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me he was robbed?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.76,0:04:09.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's check it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.94,0:04:15.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Hida{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.60,0:04:18.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you in there, Hida{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?\NHida{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.67,0:04:22.13,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Hisayoshi Minamisawa (34)\NHida Financial Employee
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.37,0:04:22.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you all doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.13,0:04:27.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your boss never showed up,\Nso we came to get him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.28,0:04:29.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's still here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.25,0:04:35.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Incidentally, what are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.20,0:04:37.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I left my cell phone here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.03,0:04:41.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah. Here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.90,0:04:42.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.90,0:04:45.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, where's your boss?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.08,0:04:47.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,His office, I'd assume.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.94,0:04:54.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir! Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.88,0:04:56.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there a master key?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.71,0:05:00.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He'd never make a master key;\Nthe vault's in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.72,0:05:03.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then we'll just have to bust it down!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.62,0:05:08.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.20,0:05:15.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No good. He's gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.93,0:05:22.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The deceased is\NMitsuhiro Hida{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, 53.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.17,0:05:25.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The cause was potassium\Ncyanide-induced suffocation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.04,0:05:30.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He died some time between\N7:00 and 7:30 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.18,0:05:31.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.11,0:05:33.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.05,0:05:37.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The key on the desk opens this door.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.42,0:05:42.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And the fact that the windows\Nwere locked from the inside
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.52,0:05:46.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,means this was an impossible crime\Nand a locked-room murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.23,0:05:53.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The security tape has\Nyou leaving at 7:04 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.97,0:06:00.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then he locks the door and returns\Nto his office to balance accounts.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.08,0:06:03.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Two hours later...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.15,0:06:06.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...you folks show up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.68,0:06:09.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who were the two people\Nwith you when you left?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.75,0:06:11.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that was—
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.92,0:06:13.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,—us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.72,0:06:16.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why'd you page me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.24,0:06:20.04,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Takako Fujii (29)\NHida Financial Employee
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.86,0:06:21.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was having fun\Ndoing karaoke with friends!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.24,0:06:23.71,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Hiroshi Iino (31)\NHida Financial Employee
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.06,0:06:23.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What exactly is going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.97,0:06:28.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone murdered your boss!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.94,0:06:35.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph. So the cretin finally\Ngot what he deserved.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.21,0:06:37.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.81,0:06:41.21,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}There sure is a lot\Nof money strewn about!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.95,0:06:45.72,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He's biting his nails.\NIs it a habit of his?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.72,0:06:47.02,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Habit?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.02,0:06:50.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, did your boss have any habits?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.01,0:06:50.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Habits?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.89,0:06:54.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Like when he counts money\Nor something...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.03,0:06:58.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it,\Nhe always spread the bills like a fan
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.40,0:07:01.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and then licked his\Nright thumb like so.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.47,0:07:06.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who gave these bills to him?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.58,0:07:07.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I did...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.01,0:07:11.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then it's simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.35,0:07:14.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer was you, Iino{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.25,0:07:17.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You laced the bills with poison in advance!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.65,0:07:19.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's crazy!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.05,0:07:20.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.86,0:07:25.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As Detective Mouri said, poison was\Nfound on the victim's right thumb
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.33,0:07:27.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and several of the bills.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.20,0:07:29.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What'd I tell ya!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.20,0:07:34.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,However, the poison on the bills\Nwas shaped like his thumbprint,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.07,0:07:38.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so it was likely his thumb\Nthat put it there...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.04,0:07:39.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're sure about that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.85,0:07:40.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.01,0:07:44.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Coffee...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.55,0:07:48.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the coffee I gave him\Njust before I left for the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.72,0:07:50.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then YOU'RE the killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.52,0:07:53.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You probably smeared poison\Nall over the cup handle!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.62,0:07:58.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no poison was found\Non the cup or in the coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.16,0:07:59.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.90,0:08:05.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We only found poison on the\Nvictim's thumb, several bills,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.13,0:08:06.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and two other places—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.90,0:08:11.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the inside door knob\Nand the lock above it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.91,0:08:13.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.34,0:08:17.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But just like on the bills, the poison\Nwas in the shape of his thumbprint,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.58,0:08:20.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so it seems he touched them\Nwith the poison on his thumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.92,0:08:25.79,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Come to think of it, he said the\Nvictim was flustered on the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.79,0:08:30.76,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What if he left the room halfway\Nthrough counting the money,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.76,0:08:35.20,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}touched something with poison on it,\Nreturned to this room,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.20,0:08:37.80,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and locked the door?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.80,0:08:41.64,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But how'd they get him\Nto touch whatever it was?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.64,0:08:45.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope you haven't touched\Nanything since you arrived!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.54,0:08:49.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,All I've touched\Nwas this cell phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.88,0:08:52.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,May I hold on to that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.62,0:08:53.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.72,0:08:56.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's that woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.90,0:08:58.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.92,0:09:03.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, now! What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.56,0:09:06.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it obvious? I'm making tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.43,0:09:09.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You fool! Don't touch ANYTHING!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.43,0:09:11.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.14,0:09:17.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You haven't touched anything else,\Nhave you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.24,0:09:20.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I used the restroom\Nwhen I got here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.24,0:09:23.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And I used it after her...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.61,0:09:25.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Anything else?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.51,0:09:28.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I used the computer\Na little bit...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.95,0:09:33.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You! No dropping ashes here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.00,0:09:42.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Happy now, Mr. Detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.40,0:09:46.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.94,0:09:48.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.91,0:09:55.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.24,0:09:59.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're all suspects! No wandering around!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.05,0:10:07.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oops, I turned it on...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.82,0:10:11.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Think it's OK to shut it off?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.30,0:10:12.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dunno...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.53,0:10:14.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't touch that!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.56,0:10:18.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll shut it off!\NJust don't touch anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.13,0:10:23.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, one wrong key press\Nand they'll find your data...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.84,0:10:28.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The records of you\Nembezzling company money.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.04,0:10:29.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Embezzling?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.23,0:10:31.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No! I haven't done anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.21,0:10:34.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me you killed him\Nbecause he found out!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.68,0:10:36.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's absurd!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.38,0:10:40.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,YOU wanted to kill him too,\NMinamisawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.69,0:10:44.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You were in tears\Nwhen he blamed you
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.93,0:10:48.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,for a client defaulting on\Na big loan!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.83,0:10:55.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,YOU were always wishing\Nhow he'd die already!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.34,0:10:57.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.17,0:11:01.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But if a borrower isn't gonna repay,\Nhe shouldn't borrow at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.68,0:11:06.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You found no poison\Nanywhere in the office?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.62,0:11:09.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Not even the restroom or break room?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.09,0:11:09.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.78,0:11:13.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was potassium cyanide\Nthe victim touched.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.69,0:11:17.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be wiped cleanly away\Non such short notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.03,0:11:22.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means it's on\None of you three!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.23,0:11:26.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have to ask each of you\Nto empty your pockets.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.23,0:11:28.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You first, Minamisawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.20,0:11:29.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.00,0:11:34.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A wallet, watch, house key, notebook,\Ntrain pass, and handkerchief.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.24,0:11:37.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The handkerchief is a little damp.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.91,0:11:40.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Because I just used the restroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.12,0:11:41.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Next is Fujii{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.85,0:11:45.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Your handkerchief is damp, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.15,0:11:48.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Obviously. I also used the restroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.49,0:11:50.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're next, Iino{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.20,0:11:51.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.29,0:11:54.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And another damp handkerchief.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.53,0:11:57.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, but yours is sopping wet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.73,0:11:59.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I tend to sweat a lot...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.97,0:12:06.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,None of their things came out positive?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.68,0:12:11.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No. Absolutely no poison was found.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.08,0:12:14.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'll be taking my things back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.48,0:12:16.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine with you, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.26,0:12:18.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.49,0:12:22.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}. Let's go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.09,0:12:23.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, I still—
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.73,0:12:28.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Say, that person's been\Nlike that this whole time...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.63,0:12:30.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! Could it be?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.87,0:12:32.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.43,0:12:34.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Mister Examiner!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.20,0:12:37.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You said you checked everything\Nthe victim might've touched, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.77,0:12:38.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.61,0:12:40.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you check for fingerprints, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.21,0:12:41.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.21,0:12:43.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, what if—
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.05,0:12:48.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! I thought it\Nwas strange, myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.55,0:12:49.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.95,0:12:53.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.05,0:12:56.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They're gonna get mad\Nif you poke around there!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.73,0:12:58.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.96,0:13:01.46,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Found it! Bleach!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.46,0:13:06.07,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The spill-off is fresh!\NThe killer used this!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.07,0:13:07.94,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That person's actions,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.94,0:13:09.47,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}the unnatural fingerprints,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.47,0:13:11.70,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and the time they\Nentered the restroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.74,0:13:18.55,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}They manipulated and poisoned the victim\Nin this otherwise empty office!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.55,0:13:21.34,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}As if by magic!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.86,0:13:27.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.59,0:13:29.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sneaking around again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.96,0:13:31.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran! Take him home already!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.86,0:13:33.35,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}No choice!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.83,0:13:38.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.83,0:13:41.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.04,0:13:43.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You know who did it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.34,0:13:46.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. The killer's aim\Nwas a locked-room murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.84,0:13:51.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran. Return to my office and get\Nthe iodine from the first-aid kit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.48,0:13:52.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.68,0:13:57.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer's identity will\Nemerge once we have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.49,0:13:59.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,OK! I'll be right back!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.62,0:14:07.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer got the victim to leave\Nthe room halfway through his counting
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.16,0:14:09.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and got him to touch\Nsomething with poison on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.70,0:14:15.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was after he returned and\Nlocked the door that he was poisoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.20,0:14:19.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer used the victim's habit\Nof licking his right thumb
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.94,0:14:22.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,before counting money.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.55,0:14:27.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In which case, the killer was\None of you three employees
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.08,0:14:31.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,who knew of his habit\Nand what he was doing tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.72,0:14:36.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on! No poison was\Nfound outside this room!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.86,0:14:40.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, how did the killer\Nget him to touch it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.53,0:14:46.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A certain something would make\N10 out of 10 people do the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.84,0:14:50.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it! The phone!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.87,0:14:54.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone would pick up\Na ringing phone!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.38,0:14:55.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Minamisawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.48,0:15:01.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet you called from outside so he'd\Npick up your poison-covered phone!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.62,0:15:04.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Not so.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.02,0:15:07.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Minamisawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} bites his nails.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.69,0:15:13.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yet, when he came to get his phone,\Nhe picked it up with his bare hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.83,0:15:19.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Had there been poison, he'd have\Nbeen too afraid to do such a thing
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.10,0:15:22.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,because there'd be no telling\Nwhere it had been touched.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.30,0:15:24.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The computer, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.61,0:15:30.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Iino{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! You had him turn it on\Nto check some data, didn't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.58,0:15:31.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.98,0:15:33.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm afraid not.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.78,0:15:37.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There'd be no guarantee\Nhe'd turn it on with his thumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.79,0:15:40.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what was the poison on?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.19,0:15:44.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There was a way to make him touch\Nsomething with his right thumb
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.99,0:15:47.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,whether he wanted to or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.27,0:15:51.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There it is now!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.53,0:15:56.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The demonic call the killer\Nused to lead him to his death!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.14,0:16:02.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.70,0:16:04.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the teapot!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.02,0:16:08.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The teapot?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.02,0:16:14.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Aha! That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.82,0:16:18.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer put poison\Non the knob here!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.79,0:16:20.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that right, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.43,0:16:21.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.50,0:16:25.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Gas stoves on the market are\Nusually for right-handers.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.20,0:16:32.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Poison left on the left side of\Nthe knob would be touched by a thumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.64,0:16:39.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As proof, only this door's\Ninside knob had poison on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.72,0:16:43.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means he rushed out\Nwithout closing the door,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.99,0:16:47.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,touched the poison\Nin his flustered state,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.79,0:16:51.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,then closed it when he returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.43,0:16:56.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So who used that trick\Nto poison the president?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.93,0:16:59.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The only one who got\Nnear the stove afterwards...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.80,0:17:03.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...you, Takako Fujii{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.54,0:17:09.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Just before you left,\Nyou put the teapot on the stove
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.14,0:17:15.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so the whistle would sound\Nwhile he was counting the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.02,0:17:19.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You planned to wipe\Nthe poison away tomorrow,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.36,0:17:24.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but his body was found earlier than\Nexpected and the police showed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.53,0:17:30.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Afraid the poison on the stove\Nknob would be discovered,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.00,0:17:34.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you entered the break room and\Nwiped it off with your handkerchief.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.77,0:17:41.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How's that? You said yourself it\Ncouldn't be wiped away so soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.31,0:17:45.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it {\i1}is{\i0} impossible. Assuming it\Nwas an ordinary handkerchief.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.08,0:17:49.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I brought the iodine, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.62,0:17:51.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Iodine?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.22,0:17:57.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, then, Inspector. Please put\Nsome iodine on her damp handkerchief.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.33,0:18:01.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A single drop will\Nshed light on everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.54,0:18:11.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just going to\Nmake a brown stain...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.55,0:18:18.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The color disappeared!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.35,0:18:24.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Soaked into her handkerchief\Nis neither water nor sweat!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.45,0:18:26.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's sodium thiosulfate!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.69,0:18:28.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sodium thiosulfate?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.69,0:18:33.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A bleach used to remove color\Nfrom disinfectants like iodine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.93,0:18:39.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's also an antidote that neutralizes\Nthe effects of potassium cyanide!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.67,0:18:42.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's still some\Nin the restroom cabinet!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.07,0:18:47.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Bleach with a special chemical that\Nreacts at room temperature, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.54,0:18:49.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}! Check it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.13,0:18:50.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.21,0:18:56.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After the police found out, Fujii{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nlikely went straight to the restroom
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.15,0:19:00.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and soaked her\Nhandkerchief in the bleach.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.33,0:19:07.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe I was\Nfound out so quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.86,0:19:09.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Fujii{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.20,0:19:11.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So you did do it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.17,0:19:16.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. I killed\Nthat devious money-fiend.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.81,0:19:19.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.68,0:19:22.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Easy. My man borrowed money from him
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.41,0:19:25.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,then hung himself when\Nhe couldn't pay it back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.81,0:19:27.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's that simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.52,0:19:32.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But you were always saying\Nhow borrowing money is wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.12,0:19:35.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I wouldn't have\Nbothered with revenge
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.09,0:19:40.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,had he borrowed money for a car,\Na house, or gambling,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.43,0:19:43.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but it was for my sake,\Nso I had no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.50,0:19:45.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your sake?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.10,0:19:48.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I've always had a weak heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.07,0:19:51.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and I was in the hospital between\Nmy college graduation and 3 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.71,0:19:55.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My parents died early on and I had\Nno friends because of my attitude,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.81,0:19:58.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so only he ever visited me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.51,0:20:01.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He said he'd pay the\Nhospital bills somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.42,0:20:05.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When I finally got better\Nand went to his apartment,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.25,0:20:10.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I found him dead with a\NHida Financial loan form at his feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.99,0:20:13.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So you joined the company\Nto get revenge?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.90,0:20:17.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep. I waited for my\Nchance this whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.47,0:20:21.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, Detective.\NHow did you know I did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.54,0:20:28.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That'd be because of the left hand\Nyou kept in your coat the entire time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.34,0:20:33.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You always used your right hand to\Ntake out cigarettes or use a lighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.75,0:20:37.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You used your left hand only once\Nto turn the stove knob.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.89,0:20:42.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a heavy smoker.\NYou touch your lips when you smoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.82,0:20:48.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Afraid of that, you purposely\Nturned the knob with your left hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.30,0:20:52.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, you kept your\Nleft hand in your pocket
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.13,0:20:58.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so you wouldn't accidentally\Nsmear the poison on anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.31,0:21:02.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And to think my man\Ngot me to stop smoking...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.48,0:21:05.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He must be laughing\Nin the next world...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.06,0:22:36.48,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Arcade"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.17,0:22:37.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Kogoro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.11,0:22:40.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't see you here too often!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.24,0:22:41.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.98,0:22:46.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody'll play with me 'cuz it\Nreminds them of what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.78,0:22:50.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So you bring a kid with you\Nto play Strip Mahjong?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.25,0:22:52.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! Perfect!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.25,0:22:55.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,OK! Now {\i1}chi-so-ki{\i0} for a {\i1}dama-ten{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.39,0:22:58.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Moron! Go for the {\i1}sha-ki{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.59,0:23:00.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just what are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.93,0:23:02.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, well, you see—
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.70,0:23:07.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You need to lose the {\i1}pa-so{\i0} and use\Nthe {\i1}dora-so-machi{\i0} to get a {\i1}soku-ri{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.30,0:23:11.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,(one tile to win)
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.30,0:23:11.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Riichi{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.27,0:23:12.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Move!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.64,0:23:14.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,OK! Bring it on!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.58,0:23:18.14,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10\a7}Yeah, right. You got an {\i1}an-ko{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.58,0:23:18.14,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10\a1}Yeah, right. You got an {\i1}an-ko{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.82,0:23:21.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,(wild tile)
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.82,0:23:21.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Tsumo{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.18,0:23:24.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A {\i1}riichi{\i0}, {\i1}ippatsu tsumo{\i0},\N{\i1}hon-itsu{\i0}, and 4 {\i1}doras{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.85,0:23:29.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Even an {\i1}ura-dora{\i0}!\NHurray! A {\i1}sanbaiman{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.62,0:23:31.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,OK! Last one!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.96,0:23:36.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who in the world\Ntaught you Mahjong?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.23,0:23:38.29,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10\an8}Heck if I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.23,0:23:38.29,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10\a2}Heck if I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.71,0:23:51.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Shin'ichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.55,0:23:56.22,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Kaitō #1412, who toys with\Npolice the country over...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.22,0:23:58.81,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}AKA "Kaitō Kid!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.16,0:24:01.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.83,0:24:03.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.99,0:24:08.44,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}This is insane! No one can\Njust disappear like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.44,0:24:14.41,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan Special:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.41,0:24:19.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's Special Hint: Pearl
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.59,0:24:20.19,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time is—
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.19,0:24:21.29,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a special, Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.29,0:24:22.89,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not in it, Detective Takagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.89,0:24:23.67,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Neither are you, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.67,0:24:24.23,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
